commit_message:
Revert "Fixes Python 3 str issue in ConfigDrive creation"

This reverts commit 0134d88b750c304fa893ed4778806e56ec410857.

The commit was breaking tripleo-ci on stable/liberty with this error: AttributeError: 'module' object has no attribute 'dump_as_bytes'

The root cause is that jsonutils.py from the stable/liberty version of oslo.serialization does not have a dump_as_bytes method.

Change-Id: Ib68d80dd946fe447e51652ea9fcf5fe69fe30903

commit_message:
Fixes Python 3 str issue in ConfigDrive creation

ConfigDrive creation fails on Python 3 when writing metadata to file
due to the fact that in Python 3 only bytes can be written to a file.

This patch fixes this issue by replacing jsonutils.dumps with
jsonutils.dump_as_bytes and thus ensuring that all data that is to
be written is bytes and not str.

Change-Id: Ie84f8badb185295fe019d80f8036aeb941709342
Closes-Bug: #1502583
(cherry picked from commit f395f457976fe7e5b91aa6c0910f790efe9be221)

commit_message:
Upgrade all packages after puppet managed ones

This updates tripleo::packages so that when enable_upgrade
is used it will:

 1) upgrade puppet managed packages (will trigger puppet dependencies)
 2) then upgrade all packages via exec
 3) then restart services

NOTE: the intention here is that the Exec['update-packages'] will
always execute if enable_upgrade is set. It is not idempotent
in this regard because I think we always want to execute it
if enable_upgrade is set.

Change-Id: I02f7cf07792765359f19fdf357024d9e48690e42
Related-bug: #1522943

commit_message:
Constraint based experimental jobs for neutron-vpnaas

Adding additional experimental jobs for neutron-vpnaas repo for
running with constraints.  This is the first step, in adding
constraint based support to neutron-vpnaas.  Later commits will
update tox.ini in the repo to support the new jobs, make the
jobs non-voting and runnable for releases after Kilo, and then
make the jobs voting.

Removed jobs that don't currently work:
 - gate-grenade-dsvm-neutron-vpnaas
 - gate-tempest-dsvm-neutron-pg-full

This will be the template for what we can do for other advanced
services too.

Change-Id: I3a2c3c81533ce6145cd16c2a08a4a2af0dfb0d07
Partial-Bug: #1522503

commit_message:

commit_message:
Experimental datastores use new service commands

Make the experimental datastores (leaving Vertica/DB2 for experts :-) )
use the new generic service commands to start/stop/restart database.

This should simplify testing, help to consolidate the log messages
and reduce the codebase across those datastores.

The dbaas test was updated with a generic BaseAppTest
to cover common codepaths. The datastores now use this
common base instead of duplicating the tests.
The Redis call to start database was also renamed from
'start_redis' to 'start_db' to match other datastores and
simplify further testing.

Also discovered and fixed a couple of Postgres-related issues:
- Postgres is missing service tests.
- Postgres Manager does not pass the manager name on its base.

Change-Id: Ifb77f270db1d6f731a61e546020122d552611ed9
Partial-Bug: 1515716

commit_message:
Use keystoneauth instead of keystoneclient

keystoneauth was split out last cycle as a library specifically to deal
with doing auth functions so that people who do not need to do keystone
CRUD operations can just consume only the auth session parts. As part
of modernizing keystone interactions, use keystoneauth instead of
keystoneclient.

Change-Id: Ieae0773ebbb8655ed79d496dd393482e2792e404

commit_message:
config-reference: Added tgz compressed image upload option

Stated in the hypervisor-xen-api that If one desires to

commit_message:
Optimise the workers used for all services for the AIO

The current default number of worker threads for the AIO consumes too many
resources, resulting in gate check failures.

This patch implements a set of sane defaults for the AIO, reducing the
number of workers for most services to 2.

Implements: blueprint gate-split
Change-Id: I553c6aa8711fa85434547585d3a56cca47539fa0

commit_message:
Fix bind mount permission error for glance api container

To allow chown command to take effect for bind mount in the
container, the directory on the host should have the same user and
group name. Otherwise, we can not assign correct file permission
in the container

Change-Id: If2e6126281955445135fb48a1055f37e23d17044
Closes-Bug: #1519965

commit_message:
Create unaddressed port from network with subnet

Currently neutron could create port from a network with subnet, but
with {"port": {"fixed_ips": [{}]}}, it still can't create unaddressed
port. This patch add some verification for it.

Partially Implements: blueprint vm-without-l3-address

Change-Id: Iebfa203d4a507c2e66589b21ae10929784cbffdd

subject: Move to [oslo_messaging_rabbit]
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-12-30 09:25:10.000000000', 'files': ['etc/designate/designate.conf.sample'], 'message': 'Move to [oslo_messaging_rabbit]

Oslo_config separated some special groups ( or sections called in
config file), such as 'oslo_messaging_qpid', 'oslo_messaging_rabbit'
and 'oslo_messaging_amqp'. Oslo_config load relevant options from
corresponding groups instead of DEFAULT.
If the options are left in the [DEFAULT] section, we may get a
warning in the log like this:
WARNING oslo_config.cfg [-] Option "rabbit_password" from group
"DEFAULT" is deprecated. Use option "rabbit_password" from group
"oslo_messaging_rabbit".

refer to:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/173312/

Change-Id: I077d5d47b48de49e4b8354bef5fb68ffdfcb2733
'}]
commit_message:
Move to [oslo_messaging_rabbit]

Oslo_config separated some special groups ( or sections called in
config file), such as 'oslo_messaging_qpid', 'oslo_messaging_rabbit'
and 'oslo_messaging_amqp'. Oslo_config load relevant options from
corresponding groups instead of DEFAULT.
If the options are left in the [DEFAULT] section, we may get a
warning in the log like this:
WARNING oslo_config.cfg [-] Option "rabbit_password" from group
"DEFAULT" is deprecated. Use option "rabbit_password" from group
"oslo_messaging_rabbit".

refer to:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/173312/

Change-Id: I077d5d47b48de49e4b8354bef5fb68ffdfcb2733

subject: Container-Sync to check the right client exception
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-12-21 20:15:13.000000000', 'files': ['swift/container/sync.py', 'test/unit/container/test_sync.py'], 'message': 'Container-Sync to check the right client exception

The sync daemon uses SimpleClient to do delete and put
to the remote proxy. simpleClient uses urllib2 to do
HTTP requests and as such raises urllib2.HTTPError

The sync daemon, however, catches ClientException.
Thus, the sync daemon does not e.g. recognize that
a delete ended up with 404 and
(1) continues to replicate
(2) does not progress sync_point2

Change-Id: Ie1d05d66a8be93b83ba604993500e55500c7eac5
Closes-Bug: #1419901
'}]
commit_message:
Container-Sync to check the right client exception

The sync daemon uses SimpleClient to do delete and put
to the remote proxy. simpleClient uses urllib2 to do
HTTP requests and as such raises urllib2.HTTPError

The sync daemon, however, catches ClientException.
Thus, the sync daemon does not e.g. recognize that
a delete ended up with 404 and
(1) continues to replicate
(2) does not progress sync_point2

Change-Id: Ie1d05d66a8be93b83ba604993500e55500c7eac5
Closes-Bug: #1419901

commit_message:
Set nova ironic admin_url correctly

Update our nova.conf ironic config section so that we properly set
the admin_url. Previously it would always be localhost (which
isn't always what we bind to).

This patch also moves the nova::compute::ironic settings into
hiera.

Change-Id: Ic42f1af5b66acf187715599f72ddf983fefb33c7
(cherry picked from commit 67d721b2398eca4588908e478f0991e51e9f11f3)

commit_message:
Put py34 first in the env order of tox

To solve the problem of "db type could
not be determined" on py34 we have to run first the py34 env to, then, run
py27. This patch puts py34 first on the tox.ini list of envs to avoid this
problem to happen.

Change-Id: Iff88d06033f998d5e1ab84cac00e40bf516cd6b3
Closes-bug: #1489059

commit_message:
Add check for sufficient memory to undercloud install

It turns out that it is possible to install the undercloud on a
2 GB system, but it will cause all kinds of weird problems and not
perform well.  Let's be explicit about our requirements and refuse
to install in such an environment.

Change-Id: I7aae41b57cb82e1d776b200ff56fd90756eff19e

commit_message:
Check for migration branch dir

Currently, neutron_migrations_facts ensures the migrations dir exists,
but doesn't check if the branch dir for the given release exists.  This
commit updates neutron_migrations_facts to handle cases where a branch
dir may not exist (as is the case on mitaka).

Change-Id: I4b0d15ae6a0c2a840e66f81994f0956382130abc
Closes-Bug: #1527582

1) Fix the cluster comminication test.
   Replace the old way of testing an existing cluster by
   creating a database on the cluster and checking its existence

   Use the 'test_helper' infrastructure to test operations on an actual

commit_message:
Finish cluster int-tests

1) Fix the cluster comminication test.
   Replace the old way of testing an existing cluster by
   creating a database on the cluster and checking its existence
   afterwards, which is not compatible with datastores that do not
   support databases.
   Use the 'test_helper' infrastructure to test operations on an actual
   data set - the same method used by single-instance tests as well.

2) Add missing int-tests for cluster grow and shrink operations.
   The test verifies data operations after grow and shrink
   operations respectively.

3) Move the Redis and PXC cluster tests to the new framework.

4) Make cluster tests independent of instance test by deriving
   them from 'base' rather than 'instance_create' test group -
   - i.e. no need to run instance tests for clusters.

5) Added (disabled until https://review.openstack.org/#/c/224363/
   merges) code to create a helper user/database on a cluster.

6) Added test flags:
       - TESTS_USE_CLUSTER_ID
       - TESTS_DO_NOT_DELETE_CLUSTER

Change-Id: I4c97c77669b56295745fa2af8bb14f07ac52dd7a

commit_message:
Add ip addresses to horizon allowed_hosts

This will make it so that you can connect to Horizon on the undercloud
using an IP address instead of just the fqdn. To get the ip addresses,
we use the known value of the ip address on the ctlplane network
(LOCAL_IP).

Change-Id: Ifdace3e29fc61afdbd88b228c772881837b3190a

commit_message:
Update os_database_connection with extra param

Add support for providing additional parameters to be used when
constructing the database uri. This change adds an 'extra' parameter
which is a hash that will be joined together when constructing the
database uri. It should be noted that the charset option, which can be
provided as a standalone option, will override charset when passed in
the 'extra' parameter. This is to maintain backwards compatibility.

Usage Example:
  os_database_connection({
    ...
    extra => { 'charset' => 'utf-8', 'read_timeout' => 60 }
  })

Change-Id: I7ef078b76ac6cd7bea42a0ac92b383cefd47167a
Co-Authored-By: Alex Schultz <aschultz@mirantis.com>
(cherry picked from commit bad1c6514a896532114703bdc2abd59edbf124a1)

revisions:

By default, if the same role is called in ansible it will only run
once per node. Due to how we have the inventory setup ansible views
every service as a different node and will try to run the common role
tasks again. This causes slowdown in all cases but is particularly
noticable when pulling images. A small change will ensure these tasks
only run once per node per run as originally intended.

TrivialFix

Change-Id: I20b9c46991d10176c8f8645a335eb7a9ed750ee3
'}]
commit_message:
Simulate normal ansible behaviour with shared role

By default, if the same role is called in ansible it will only run
once per node. Due to how we have the inventory setup ansible views
every service as a different node and will try to run the common role
tasks again. This causes slowdown in all cases but is particularly
noticable when pulling images. A small change will ensure these tasks
only run once per node per run as originally intended.

TrivialFix

Change-Id: I20b9c46991d10176c8f8645a335eb7a9ed750ee3

commit_message:
Refactor openstack-network: move ml2 plugin into server-config.pp

Currently openstack-network-server-config task is not idempotent - it
unconditionally stops the neutron-server service upon invocation relying
on plugins/ml2.pp to bring it up once the plugin config is materialized.

This patch refactors openstack-network/{server-config,plugins/ml2}.pp so
the plugin configuration is now an essential part of server-config.pp.

commit_message:
Remove hardcoded network roles from HAproxy manifests

This commit removed some hardcoded network roles from HAproxy manifests
and replaces them with globals. Also it fixes hiera override functionality
for some globals.

Change-Id: Ia6006b19f366cec8ac686e19e7b921e95051c1ac
Closes-Bug: #1505604

commit_message:
Chown /var/lib/glance on every run of glance-api

Currently, Docker doesn't support user mounts. Every time
you're running any Docker container with mount, the mounted
directory inside container belongs to root.

Before this change, chmod of /var/lib/glance was done only
on bootstrap. Therefore, the actually running glance-api
container was unable to write here.

Change-Id: I16f966b05e4373b715e2ed4ae80cc334a2804dd7
Closes-Bug: 1519965

commit_message:
WSGI enfore fails should return 403 instead of 500

When user is not authorized to perform operations defined in policy
file, it should return a 403 error. The 500 error is incorrect.
This patch do the following changes:
1. Raise a PolicyNotAuthorized 403 exception when normal user
without admin privilege run command 'magnum service-list'.
2. Remove unnecessary hacking rule M301 'decorator must be
the first decorator on a method'.
3. Fix failed enforcement test cases introduced by 403
PolicyNotAuthorized exception.

Change-Id: Ie5a7d138cdb8b226686c189ae86f251c0a1329c8
Closes-Bug: #1520311

commit_message:
Add extension_manager and support for extensions in linuxbridge agent

There is extensions mechanism for l2 agents already but it was
implemented only for openvswitch l2 agent. This patch adds support for
such extensions also for linuxbridge agent.

This patch also adds support for network_update events received by the
agent via RPC. It is required because sometimes when a network is
updated (for example with a QoS policy is attached to it) all ports that
belong to the network should also be updated.

Change-Id: Ie81c818d0eb817b044a6df1cbddc5864f118fe3f
Partial-bug: 1468803

commit_message:
Fix CI Tempest jobs

After merge of change [1] to devstack project, preconfigured creds for
Tempest cannot be used anymore. But Manila requires such.
For the moment, latest Tempest interfaces cannot allow us to use
preconfigured creds because of bug #1524717.
So, until this bug fixed, we should workaround Devstack changes and
set legacy opts explicitly.

Also, redefine new Nutron option 'dnsmasq_local_resolv' to 'False' value,
that is 'True' by default and was added in change [2].
Default value causes Nova operations initiated by Manila be very slow.
That leads to breakage of CI.

[1] I65b56ff681d6c27094380693c953fbc3664eceb0
[2] I17a884f467d307432a06f67a9dd93ed2fa6081a3

Change-Id: I516a6c9ab4396b14e3984d5f810210e4fcf7ec85
Related-Bug: #1531049
Closes-Bug: #1530847

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-01-07 08:49:22.000000000', 'files': ['os_brick/tests/initiator/test_connector.py', 'os_brick/initiator/connector.py'], 'message': 'remove unneeded in_use flag checking for multipath

In iSCSI connector, _disconnect_volume_multipath_iscsi() checks
if no other multipath device attached has the iqn and portal
as same as the detaching multipath device.
The checking code using in_use flag depends on persistent-named symbolic
links("/dev/disk/by-path/ip-*") for iSCSI devices which constitute
the detaching multipath device. However, the links are deleted in
advance of calling _disconnect_volume_multipath_iscsi().
So, the checking code wouldn't work properly and should be fixed
in proper way.

The proper way is to just check whether the discovered iSCSI targets
via sendtargets discovery associate with iSCSI block devices
("/dev/disk/by-path/ip-*") or not.
If the target doesn't associate with any iSCSI block device, the target
is never used by anyone and can be disconnected.

This patch removes the in_use flag checking in
_disconnect_volume_multipath_iscsi() and the related codes.
The other codes in _disconnect_volume_multipath_iscsi are valid.

Partial-Bug: 1487169
Change-Id: I70cf5e1990cc5baffb3ef5150b9ed673e3504d6c
'}]
commit_message:
remove unneeded in_use flag checking for multipath

In iSCSI connector, _disconnect_volume_multipath_iscsi() checks
if no other multipath device attached has the iqn and portal
as same as the detaching multipath device.
The checking code using in_use flag depends on persistent-named symbolic
links("/dev/disk/by-path/ip-*") for iSCSI devices which constitute
the detaching multipath device. However, the links are deleted in
advance of calling _disconnect_volume_multipath_iscsi().
So, the checking code wouldn't work properly and should be fixed
in proper way.

The proper way is to just check whether the discovered iSCSI targets
via sendtargets discovery associate with iSCSI block devices
("/dev/disk/by-path/ip-*") or not.
If the target doesn't associate with any iSCSI block device, the target
is never used by anyone and can be disconnected.

This patch removes the in_use flag checking in
_disconnect_volume_multipath_iscsi() and the related codes.
The other codes in _disconnect_volume_multipath_iscsi are valid.

Partial-Bug: 1487169
Change-Id: I70cf5e1990cc5baffb3ef5150b9ed673e3504d6c

http://127.0.0.1:5000) in clouds.yaml, those request will return 404.

Why those request will return 404? Because of keystoneclient will assume
auth_url will point to identity version 2.0 api. It will make

commit_message:
Using openstackclient instead of keystoneclient

Some functional test will use keystoneclient to get tenant's
id. If user didn't specify identity version for auth_url(such as
http://127.0.0.1:5000) in clouds.yaml, those request will return 404.

Why those request will return 404? Because of keystoneclient will assume
auth_url will point to identity version 2.0 api. It will make
authentication request to url, which is just auth_url + "/tokens"(such
as http://127.0.0.1:5000/tokens). We can also test that by following
command.
> keystone --os-username admin --os-tenant-name admin --os-password
admin --os-auth-url http://127.0.0.1:5000 tenant-list

Maybe we should use openstackclient instead of keystoneclient.

Change-Id: Id0b14ff7e38028a403ad15e7a016990e5d230122
Closes-Bug: 1507497

commit_message:
LOG.warn -> LOG.warning

Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method, see:
https://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.html#logging.warning
so we prefer to use warning to avoid DeprecationWarning.

Change-Id: I465be390911a7c8d3c17e0a7246b960c09ab0028

commit_message:
Some small improvements on fernet uuid handling

In the review of commit Ia4a4f760d67d8bbc22759c48fc800aef016b84ed
some small improvements were noted that could be made. Namely,
attempt_convert_uuid_bytes_to_hex is no longer needed since we
know ahead of time that the conversion should work based on whether
the ID was in fact stored as bytes.

This patch also cleans up the naming of some of the fernet token
tests to be more accurate to what is being tested.

Change-Id: I74204e5b1b0e3df739fa7778ea89dcbb4501a9b9

commit_message:
LOG.warn -> LOG.warning

Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method, see:
https://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.html#logging.warning
so we prefer to use warning to avoid DeprecationWarning.

In addition to this there will be a hacking rule to prevent
this (https://review.openstack.org/#/c/262257/)

TrivialFix

Change-Id: Id1c7a5e329521b46c2fef9889861099c7a88c001

revisions:
[{'number': 10, 'created': '2015-12-15 14:05:19.000000000', 'files': ['nova/tests/unit/virt/test_hardware.py', 'nova/virt/hardware.py'], 'message': 'Fix CPU pinning for odd number of CPUs w hyperthreading

Previous logic was not handling the cases when the instance cell has an
odd number of vcpus that is larger than any sibling set on the host. The
logic would (accidentally) either reject to pin such an instance even
though there is ample free cores, or would (in case there were enough
free sibling sets on the host) spread the instance instead of pack it
onto siblings as the default policy suggests.

This patch fixes some incorrect assumptions in the code, while also
simplifying it. As an added bonus - we still attempt to expose
(via the Topology, and this time correctly) the largest possible number
of threads that we can expose to the instance.

Finally - we add some more comments to clear up the intent behind the
current packing logic with pointers how it could be tweaked to achieve
different results in the future.

Change-Id: I2c0b3b250ffb1a7483299df13b317cdb24f8141d
Co-Authored-By: Stephen Finucane <stephen.finucane@intel.com>
Closes-bug: 1501358
Closes-bug: 1467927
'}]
commit_message:
Fix CPU pinning for odd number of CPUs w hyperthreading

Previous logic was not handling the cases when the instance cell has an
odd number of vcpus that is larger than any sibling set on the host. The
logic would (accidentally) either reject to pin such an instance even
though there is ample free cores, or would (in case there were enough
free sibling sets on the host) spread the instance instead of pack it
onto siblings as the default policy suggests.

This patch fixes some incorrect assumptions in the code, while also
simplifying it. As an added bonus - we still attempt to expose
(via the Topology, and this time correctly) the largest possible number
of threads that we can expose to the instance.

Finally - we add some more comments to clear up the intent behind the
current packing logic with pointers how it could be tweaked to achieve
different results in the future.

Change-Id: I2c0b3b250ffb1a7483299df13b317cdb24f8141d
Co-Authored-By: Stephen Finucane <stephen.finucane@intel.com>
Closes-bug: 1501358
Closes-bug: 1467927

commit_message:
Fix flavor find interface function

Due to Nova API limitations, finding flavors using flavor name doesn't
work as of today. However, referencing a flavor by name instead of ID is
a common usage scenario from user's point of view. Before Nova adds
support to falvor query by name, it worth implementing a client side
filter to make SDK's interface consistent in this respect.

Change-Id: Ib74338131316c3affedd7033eeb6101458c475d7

subject: Fix broken local and global building
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-01-07 03:08:26.000000000', 'files': ['kolla/cmd/build.py'], 'message': "Fix broken local and global building

Two things broke in the related patches. This patch aims to fix that.

1) tools/build.py was no longer usable as it imported kolla from the
global pip install source. If that didnt exist (because kolla wasn't
installed with pip) then it breaks on import.

2) When kolla was installed globally it looked up the path that
matched the installation of docker-py instead of looking up a path
that had the stuff we wanted (kolla images directory)

Change-Id: I94f1856547ce54d506de72926b08c966a36ac608
Related-Id: I05f10d13e7ba1e2b985c2944aec71ce55630442b

commit_message:
Fix broken local and global building

Two things broke in the related patches. This patch aims to fix that.

1) tools/build.py was no longer usable as it imported kolla from the
global pip install source. If that didnt exist (because kolla wasn't
installed with pip) then it breaks on import.

2) When kolla was installed globally it looked up the path that
matched the installation of docker-py instead of looking up a path
that had the stuff we wanted (kolla images directory)

Change-Id: I94f1856547ce54d506de72926b08c966a36ac608
Related-Id: I05f10d13e7ba1e2b985c2944aec71ce55630442b
Related-Bug: #1530256
Closes-Bug: #1531569

subject: Fix Docker images discovery for system-wide installation
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-01-06 18:32:15.000000000', 'files': ['kolla/cmd/build.py'], 'message': "Fix Docker images discovery for system-wide installation

The Docker images discovery is assuming some directories and
'docker' suffix to be a potential directory where kolla images
may be installed by pip.

Unfortunately, in case of installation by pip as root
(system-wide), the first assumed directory was
/usr/lib/python2.7/site-packages/docker (the dir of docker-py)
instead of /usr/share/kolla/docker or
/usr/local/share/kolla/docker.

Change-Id: I597f8c56b00b7329151be438470d2032254e2e13
Closes-Bug: 1531569
"}]
commit_message:
Fix Docker images discovery for system-wide installation

The Docker images discovery is assuming some directories and
'docker' suffix to be a potential directory where kolla images
may be installed by pip.

Unfortunately, in case of installation by pip as root
(system-wide), the first assumed directory was
/usr/lib/python2.7/site-packages/docker (the dir of docker-py)
instead of /usr/share/kolla/docker or
/usr/local/share/kolla/docker.

Change-Id: I597f8c56b00b7329151be438470d2032254e2e13
Closes-Bug: 1531569

commit_message:
Use assertTrue/False(A) Methods

Specific/specialized methods are available for asserting the boolean
result in python unit test :-
1. assertTrue(expr, msg=None)
2. assertFalse(expr, msg=None)

Therefore Change assertEqual(True/False,A) to assertTrue/False(A)
as code refactoring in cinder.

Change-Id: I3c4233b0183b8949db88904c445b8c6a42247b83

Replacing range() n xrange() by six.moves.range()

To improvee consistency, use range() from six.moves

Behaves consistently like py2 xrange() n py3 range()
Re-ordered the imports alphabetically to pass pep8.

commit_message:
Put py34 first in the envlist order of tox

To solve the problem of "db type could not be determined"
on py34 we have to run first the py34 env to, then, run py27.
This patch puts py34 first on the tox.ini list
of envs to avoid this problem to happen.

Change-Id: Ifa1fadaf14269b4b1dac91657c1cf1c17891e214

commit_message:
Fix chicken and eggs problem with tripleo-heat-templates

There is a current effort on tripleo-heat-templates to manage keystone
resources directly via puppet. The effort is separate in two patchset
one to replace the current keystone.initialize() and the other other to
replace setup-endpoints().

This review is necessary in order to make CI pass the upstream jobs.
The whole keystone functions call will be removed then.

Change-Id: Ia4b3244f114dcff746ab89d355ad4933f8fdbddf

commit_message:
Change how to start the Identity service

* Sync contents with Installation Guide.
* Keystone eventlet is deprecated in favor of a separate web server
  with WSGI extensions.
  The Keystone project plans to remove eventlet support in Mitaka.
* Don't use the distribution specific command.

Closes-Bug: #1529529
Change-Id: I79ac0ed9b3a94dcc8044abc76113638e4a7206bc

[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-12-17 03:06:23.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/tests/functional/agent/l3/test_legacy_router.py', 'neutron/agent/common/ovs_lib.py'], 'message': "Separate the command for replace_port to delete and add

When a port has been added to router namespace, trying to replace the
port by adding del-port and add-port in one command, will not bring
the new port to kernel. Even if the port is updated in ovs db and can
be found on br-int, system can't see the new port. This will break
the following actions, which will manipulate the new port by ip
commands. A mail list has been filed to discuss this issue at [1].

The problem here will break the scenario that namespace is deleted
unexpectedly, and l3-agent tries to rebuild the namespace at restart.

Separating replace_port to two commands: del-port and add-port,
matches the original logic and has been verified that it can resolve
the problem here.

[1] http://openvswitch.org/pipermail/discuss/2015-December/019667.html

Change-Id: If36bcf5a0cccb667f3087aea1e9ea9f20eb3a563
Closes-Bug: #1519926
"}]
commit_message:
Separate the command for replace_port to delete and add

When a port has been added to router namespace, trying to replace the
port by adding del-port and add-port in one command, will not bring
the new port to kernel. Even if the port is updated in ovs db and can
be found on br-int, system can't see the new port. This will break
the following actions, which will manipulate the new port by ip
commands. A mail list has been filed to discuss this issue at [1].

The problem here will break the scenario that namespace is deleted
unexpectedly, and l3-agent tries to rebuild the namespace at restart.

Separating replace_port to two commands: del-port and add-port,
matches the original logic and has been verified that it can resolve
the problem here.

[1] http://openvswitch.org/pipermail/discuss/2015-December/019667.html

Change-Id: If36bcf5a0cccb667f3087aea1e9ea9f20eb3a563

commit_message:
Update designate::db class to match other module pattern

This review aims to update the designate::db class to standardize it with the
other modules db classes[1][2]. It now offers the same parameters to customize
database connection behavior.  Some internal variable naming remains
different then other modules.  This is because designate simply uses
differen config file sections[3] then other OpenStack projects.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/puppet-neutron/blob/master/manifests/db.pp
[2] https://github.com/openstack/puppet-sahara/blob/master/manifests/db.pp
[3] http://docs.openstack.org/developer/designate/install/ubuntu-kilo.html#installing-designate

Co-Authored-By: Cody Herriges <cody@puppetlabs.com>
Change-Id: Ieb841a58429564e5f13d9f683a3a9ef875f1324a

commit_message:
remove use of _get_regexes in samples tests

There was an exceptionally large amount of rote use of _get_regexes
throughout the samples tests, which doesn't provide any additional
explicitness in what's happening, and only couples the tests to the
base class in less useful ways.

Instead, when we call _verify_response, always also use the base
vanilla regexes for matching tests.

We also needed to add a few more variables to the list which always
need to be reset before testing against the static samples, because
uuids are often generated on the fly for the tests.

Lastly, test_keypairs needed some test specific surgery. It is so
highly normalized (with private test methods that take **kwargs) at
this point that it's not really clear that it's testing useful things
any more. This really needs denormalization.

Change-Id: I165b0f3aa2132373cb59982a5a5ded37b4fa1b52

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-12-09 14:59:08.000000000', 'files': ['keystone/token/providers/common.py', 'keystone/tests/unit/test_auth.py'], 'message': 'Remove comments on enforcing endpoints for trust

Back in the Grizzly version of OpenStack, we introduced Trusts
(I5745f4d9a4180b59671a143a55ed87019e98ec76).

At the time, we had an idea that we would do future work with Trusts
and Endpoints in the regard of limiting what went into Tokens. Hence we
have left TODO notes.

Change-Id: I25c606bb67a5d5b9f2194c8fb2c7df26170f88eb

commit_message:
Remove comments on enforcing endpoints for trust

Back in the Grizzly version of OpenStack, we introduced Trusts
(I5745f4d9a4180b59671a143a55ed87019e98ec76).

At the time, we had an idea that we would do future work with Trusts
and Endpoints in the regard of limiting what went into Tokens. Hence we
have left TODO notes.

Now that we have the endpoint filtering API, the old idea does not make
sense anymore.

This commit removes those invalid TODO comments.

Change-Id: I25c606bb67a5d5b9f2194c8fb2c7df26170f88eb

When Neutron is used to manage networking, the default dhcp agent
configuration does not include dns servers that would allow dnsmasq to

commit_message:
Ensure that instances can resolve external hosts

When Neutron is used to manage networking, the default dhcp agent
configuration does not include dns servers that would allow dnsmasq to
resolve external hosts.  This change adds the local system dns servers
to the dhcp agent configuration to ensure that external resolution is
possible by default.

Change-Id: Idc6a87e1d47e9a8d0c950d0d0fc6d9b4dc0df8e4
Co-Authored-By: Doug Wiegley <dougwig@parkside.io>

revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-01-07 03:00:57.000000000', 'files': ['tox.ini'], 'message': 'Put py34 first in the env order of tox and remove py33

To solve the problem of "db type could not be determined" on py34
we have to run first the py34 env to, then, run py27. This patch
puts py34 first on the tox.ini list of envs to avoid this problem
to happen. Also, as per Infra, py33 support would be removed from

'}]
commit_message:
Put py34 first in the env order of tox and remove py33

To solve the problem of "db type could not be determined" on py34
we have to run first the py34 env to, then, run py27. This patch
puts py34 first on the tox.ini list of envs to avoid this problem
to happen. Also, as per Infra, py33 support would be removed from
Mitaka, so taking care of the same as well in this patch.

Change-Id: Iae2aa78953af1bc7620462cd6762ebcd2ebc8a8f
Closes-bug: #1489059

subject: Fix socket descriptor leak
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-01-06 19:57:29.000000000', 'files': ['magnum/api/hooks.py', 'magnum/common/rpc_service.py'], 'message': 'Fix socket descriptor leak

The connection to amqp was not getting cleaned up, even after the
communication to conductor across amqp was complete, for a given
request. Thus, sockets were leaking with each communication and finally
led to a hang situation, where no more fds were available.

Change-Id: I1deabdbce6ba448fe4c25d7694aabe5e5fec7b5a
Closes-Bug: #1510776
'}]
commit_message:
Fix socket descriptor leak

The connection to amqp was not getting cleaned up, even after the
communication to conductor across amqp was complete, for a given
request. Thus, sockets were leaking with each communication and finally
led to a hang situation, where no more fds were available.

Change-Id: I1deabdbce6ba448fe4c25d7694aabe5e5fec7b5a
Closes-Bug: #1510776

commit_message:
Stop using versioned novaclient in func tests

Stop importing the versioned client and instead use the client.Client()
class to select the correct version.  The versioned client appears to be
removed from newer novaclient, breaking our tests.

Change-Id: I968be1d5c095027175d3d3c96a7e5d574b580ad7
(cherry picked from commit 9cad9fd6d0efd88478aa81515c0287b7d296df60)

commit_message:
Replace antlr3 symlinking by sys.path

For importing the correct antlr3 runtime depending on python version,
use sys.path instead of creating and deleting symlinks

Purpose: Reduce fragility and OS dependence

Partially implements blueprint: support-python3

revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-11-24 16:10:25.000000000', 'files': ['trove/tests/scenario/groups/replication_group.py', 'trove/tests/api/replication.py', 'trove/tests/scenario/runners/replication_runners.py'], 'message': "Fix race condition in replication backup delete

In the int-tests, the replication implementation verifies that the
backup used to create the replica is removed after the slave goes
active. This test runs right after the slave create, so on occasion
the backup still exists when the test runs, since the taskmanager
doesn't delete it until it also receives word that the instance is
up and running.

The test was modified to wait until the backup is gone.

The replication scenario test was also modified to include this
check at the end of its run.

Closes-Bug: #1518477
Change-Id: If815f496d6bf9111dd1f04bf02f61207a2317b2b
"}]
commit_message:
Fix race condition in replication backup delete

In the int-tests, the replication implementation verifies that the
backup used to create the replica is removed after the slave goes
active. This test runs right after the slave create, so on occasion
the backup still exists when the test runs, since the taskmanager
doesn't delete it until it also receives word that the instance is
up and running.

The test was modified to wait until the backup is gone.

The replication scenario test was also modified to include this
check at the end of its run.

Closes-Bug: #1518477
Change-Id: If815f496d6bf9111dd1f04bf02f61207a2317b2b

Remove openstack.common._i18n from Neutron

90ae25e38915cc502d9e9c52d59e8fb668a72ae1. And

commit_message:
Put py34 first in the env order of tox

To solve the problem of "db type could
not be determined" on py34 we have to run first the py34 env to, then, run
py27. This patch puts py34 first on the tox.ini list of envs to avoid this
problem to happen.

Change-Id: If022a76b2ee9a290033abc544c5fa56f1ea1e0ae
Closes-bug: #1489059

ignored. There was a note left in tox.ini to clean up the H105 issues

subject: Expire old VMs from libvirt metrics cache
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-11-23 18:42:37.000000000', 'files': ['monasca_agent/collector/checks_d/libvirt.py'], 'message': "Expire old VMs from libvirt metrics cache

This change will prevent the libvirt metrics cache from being populated
by entries from instances that are not yet active or no longer active.
Currently, the metrics cache may have both, leading to performance
issues in cases of a high VM churn.

First, VM probation testing has been moved above metric cache
initialization for each instance.  Second, before writing the metric
cache, each instance's last update time is examined.  If the instance
hasn't seen new metrics within the VM probation period, it will be
excluded from the metrics cache.  As an added precaution, in the
event that VM probation is disabled (by setting it the time to 0, as
mentioned in the documentation), this change uses the check iteration
time as a buffer to prevent active VMs from being excluded from the
cache.

A default VM probation time has been specified, too, in case the value
is missing from the configuration file.

Change-Id: I93cc42fab83cf0b6304601582f4d52b7780fe43b
"}]
commit_message:
Expire old VMs from libvirt metrics cache

This change will prevent the libvirt metrics cache from being populated
by entries from instances that are not yet active or no longer active.
Currently, the metrics cache may have both, leading to performance
issues in cases of a high VM churn.

First, VM probation testing has been moved above metric cache
initialization for each instance.  Second, before writing the metric
cache, each instance's last update time is examined.  If the instance
hasn't seen new metrics within the VM probation period, it will be
excluded from the metrics cache.  As an added precaution, in the
event that VM probation is disabled (by setting it the time to 0, as
mentioned in the documentation), this change uses the check iteration
time as a buffer to prevent active VMs from being excluded from the
cache.

A default VM probation time has been specified, too, in case the value
is missing from the configuration file.

Change-Id: I93cc42fab83cf0b6304601582f4d52b7780fe43b

subject: Improve output of host_alive plugin's ping tests
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-12-07 16:54:17.000000000', 'files': ['monasca_agent/collector/checks_d/host_alive.py'], 'message': 'Improve output of host_alive plugin's ping tests

If a ping test fails, it returns a status code != 0, which the host_alive
plugin currently uses for a catch-all "failed to execute" message in the
value_meta 'error' field.  This is wordy and confusing for ping failures.

Additionally, if the ping command fails for an OS-level problem (missing
or no longer executable), there is no handler for that exception.

This patch resolves these two issues, removes some redundant logging, and
changed the log level of a normal ping failure.

Change-Id: I038ffcdc8577bf910e8229ff06f67bcb46cac47b
'}]
commit_message:
Improve output of host_alive plugin's ping tests

If a ping test fails, it returns a status code != 0, which the host_alive
plugin currently uses for a catch-all "failed to execute" message in the
value_meta 'error' field.  This is wordy and confusing for ping failures.

Additionally, if the ping command fails for an OS-level problem (missing
or no longer executable), there is no handler for that exception.

This patch resolves these two issues, removes some redundant logging, and
changed the log level of a normal ping failure.

Change-Id: I038ffcdc8577bf910e8229ff06f67bcb46cac47b

subject: Switch Agent thread count test to global threshold
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-12-07 22:21:24.000000000', 'files': ['monasca_agent/collector/checks/services_checks.py'], 'message': 'Switch Agent thread count test to global threshold

Currently, the multi-threaded ServicesCheck class will compare the
thread number allocated to each plugin against the total number of
threads in use by the Collector.  If several ServicesCheck-based plugins
are in active use, though, a normal and reaonsable number of Collector
threads would throw an exception due to an "exploding" thread count.

This change replaces the existing apples-to-oranges thread count
comparison with one global maximum number of threads.  In the highly
unlikely event of runaway thread allocation, this would provide a level
of protection, while still allowing normal operation of a large numbe
of multithreaded plugins.

Change-Id: I263fb25fab71805a24f45e5455c79c4c2d8c81e3
'}]
commit_message:
Switch Agent thread count test to global threshold

Currently, the multi-threaded ServicesCheck class will compare the
thread number allocated to each plugin against the total number of
threads in use by the Collector.  If several ServicesCheck-based plugins
are in active use, though, a normal and reaonsable number of Collector
threads would throw an exception due to an "exploding" thread count.

This change replaces the existing apples-to-oranges thread count
comparison with one global maximum number of threads.  In the highly
unlikely event of runaway thread allocation, this would provide a level
of protection, while still allowing normal operation of a large numbe
of multithreaded plugins.

Change-Id: I263fb25fab71805a24f45e5455c79c4c2d8c81e3

commit_message:
Add `type' filter for list_credentials_for_user

When getting, or operating on a credential, EC2 controller needs to
specify it's a ec2 credential, avoiding conflicts with other type of
credentials.

Closes-Bug: #1506473
Change-Id: Id92fc87bf1be5448aa929224bbce4d3f7f4359b6

commit_message:
Optimize Taskflow storage (remove some requires parameter)

flows have been optimized to limit the amount of data being stored.
* member object is stored in flow, hence member_id can easily be retrieved
* same with vip and load_balancer

Closes-Bug: #1461686

commit_message:
Fix py34 DB issue and remove py33

To solve the problem of "db type could
not be determined" on py34 we have to run first the py34 env to, then,
run py27. This patch puts py34 first on the tox.ini list of envs to
avoid this problem to happen. py33 is not supported from Mitaka, as per
Infra, therefore removing the support for the same

Co-Authored-By: Reedip Banerjee <reedip.banerjee@nectechnologies.in>
Change-Id: Iee38f49800365b3a8f80ea78ed9945a4510c17a0
Closes-bug: #1489059

commit_message:
Add enforce_type=True in CONF.set_override

Each config option has limitation for type and value.
In production code, oslo.conf can ensure user's input
is valid, but in unit test, test methods can pass if
we use method CONF.set_override without parameter
enforce_type=True even we pass wrong type or wrong
value to config option. This commit makes sure calling
method CONF.set_override with enforce_type=True.
Closes-bug: #1517839

Change-Id: I7a4e00c0eb6423d0826eb1c1b1e1ad3da786fb52

subject: Fix bad "pool list" api v2 entry point for CLI
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-01-06 22:41:53.000000000', 'files': ['zaqarclient/queues/v2/cli.py'], 'message': 'Fix bad "pool list" api v2 entry point for CLI

Currently, when "openstack help --os-queues-api-version=2" command is
run to view all available commands of Zaqar api v2, en error is thrown
about inability to parse this entry point:
"pool_list = zaqarclient.queues.v2.cli:ListPools".

The problem occurs because "ListPool" class in zaqarclient.queues.v2.cli
package need to be called "ListPools" instead.

Renaming "ListPool" to "ListPools" will make this class properly
referred by setup.cfg and also the name of this class will be similar to
the one in zaqarclient.queues.v1.cli.
This patch is making it so.

Change-Id: I3acb0d9f1bdbe00ca2bf2de2726adf4d9f722a5c
'}]
commit_message:
Fix bad "pool list" api v2 entry point for CLI

Currently, when "openstack help --os-queues-api-version=2" command is
run to view all available commands of Zaqar api v2, en error is thrown
about inability to parse this entry point:
"pool_list = zaqarclient.queues.v2.cli:ListPools".

The problem occurs because "ListPool" class in zaqarclient.queues.v2.cli
package need to be called "ListPools" instead.

Renaming "ListPool" to "ListPools" will make this class properly
referred by setup.cfg and also the name of this class will be similar to
the one in zaqarclient.queues.v1.cli.
This patch is making it so.

Change-Id: I3acb0d9f1bdbe00ca2bf2de2726adf4d9f722a5c

commit_message:
Bump minimum oslo.config version

Ironic will make use the new feature in oslo.config to generate PortOpt

commit_message:
Add oslo.config compatibility attributes

In trying to get the OpenStack server projects to consume keystoneauth,
we ran in to the fact that they want to treat the things registered with
"register_conf_options" as oslo.config objects. It works fine that they
aren't - except that an oslo.config option has an attribute called
'deprecated_opts' while ours is called 'deprecated'. The same is true
of the other three attributes added.

Change-Id: I7d53c17d518b01946e091702a582648998c2ae17
(cherry picked from commit 25c8c5f48454cfb09169f887f01e6e56a1640d19)

commit_message:
Replace textwrap with fast standard code

This improves on commit 4350c176048b8d159d08b82b915e9544ac9dee6f

We found a major performance regression in keystoneclient
when using PKI tokens, related to http://bugs.python.org/issue25870

It can be tested with
time python -c "import textwrap; textwrap.wrap('x'*9000, 64)"

which has a complexity of O(n*n)
because it uses certain regexps in python versions before 3.5.

Closes-Bug: #1526686
Related-Bug: #1404402

Change-Id: Ibc81907c4d9db2c09fff41ccf21345fbdb19202d

commit_message:
Revert "Revert "Revert "Remove TEMPEST_CONFIG_DIR in the api tox env"""

This reverts commit be63289c273fa02159a6958e0b456d5fda217431.

Yes, it's a third order revert. Ain't it cool?

Now that tox 2.3.1 is used in gate, and it is expected to fix the issue
that we originally hacked around here, let's revert to the previous
code.

For the least, it makes API target executable locally without the need
to set TEMPEST_CONFIG_DIR in the external environment.

Also bump minimal tox version to 2.3 to avoid users hitting the old
issue with their tox 2.2.* package.

Change-Id: Ic64cb466d117ad39436cb1d079c8f5657260da2c
Related-Bug: #1515335

commit_message:
Support for multiple ldap backend.

This enable the user to inject multiple ldap backend configurations into
keystone.

Currently the ldap configuration is modeled through a class and injected
inside keystone.conf.  In a multiple domains environment, this prevents
the user to create a ldap configuration by domain.

A deprecation warning is added to the current ldap class.  This class is
not using the define as doing so would automatically trigger a restart
of the keystone server.  This would be unexpected by the openstack
operator and would certainly be seen as a bug.  This imply a lot of code
duplication but is required to make a smooth transition.

Change-Id: I75307d4a04510d8ba1a24663b1724849ea5b48f5

commit_message:
Fix Resource.__eq__ mismatch semantics of object equal

The __eq__ of apiclient.base.Resource will return True,
if the two objects have same id, even if they have different
other attributes value. The behavior is weird and don't
match the semantics of object equal. The objects that have
different value should be different objects.
Fix this issue and add some test cases in this patch.

Change-Id: I1565c6e66d6dd6cf7bd2b7e8526157190deb45de
Closes-Bug: #1499369

commit_message:
Fixes query.one() return usage in endpoint-policy

The return of get_policy_association(..) is a
dict in the form {'policy_id': policy_id}.
However, its return should be a PolicyAssociation
dict, since it is what is returned as a list by
the list operation.

Closes-Bug: #1483375

Change-Id: Ibe5eef68ad9c60ba5c0d7671f4a1a676b842fded

commit_message:
Add keystone domain specific configuration.

Implements blueprint keystone-domain-configuration

Adds a provider able to configure multiple domains and two parameters in
keystone class to setup a working multi-domains configuration.

The keystone_config type has been refactored into a mixin to be shared
by keystone_config and keystone_domain_config.

The provider, even though it is inheriting from openstack_config (and
not keystone_config because it hard code the path), has required more
new code.  The problem is that we have several configuration files to
work with (one per domain) which is unusual.

The self.prefetch method is required to check the current catalog.  If
it's changing the Keystone_config[identity/domain_config_dir] we take it
directly into account without the need for another run.

Keystone_config[identity/domain_config_dir] configuration and the
associated directory are autorequired.

Change-Id: I5e4b298460ee592640af59ac9dcbefa3daf98098

ensure devstack is using correct branch

devstack-gate does not know how to handle independently released
projects. because of this, it is incapable of cloning the stable

commit_message:
Raise not found error if stack is deleted when find_stack

If find_stack with id, heat will always return the stack body
even if the stack is deleted, so we won't receive a not found
error. This patch will check stack status and raise not found
error if stack is deleted.

Change-Id: I848a304b83ec89e01564302094c30f488116bda5
Closes-Bug: #1528996

commit_message:
Make Keystone_endpoint match service by name/type

Since a chance in puppet-keystone (1], we now match an endpoint with a
service name/type.
)
[1] http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/puppet-keystone/commit/?id=0a4e06abb0f5b3f324464ff5219d2885816311ce

Also:
require package before config file Before trying to build the guestagent
config file from the template with Puppet, first install the package so
we make sure /etc/trove is ready. Otherwise, Puppet will randomly fail
to create the file, if the package is not installed yet.

We need to squash the two changes otherwise CI will never pass.
Change-Id: I9662c684c83933ffe6ede0337bc1770dd65b0ce7
Closes-Bug: #1528308
(cherry picked from commit c73c228ae73062ddf421a4a74748f9cf0066cbc8)

commit_message:
Fix timeline rendering in Firefox.

Firefox appears to behave differently than Chrome when computing CSS
sizes for SVG elements, causing the timeline elements to have
incorrect widths. This modifies layout behavior to use only attribute
sizes instead of CSS sizes, which works around the issue.

Change-Id: I6af2d9502ba7881c630197494382c0bc7eec8283

commit_message:
Add key-listener to refactored timeline

This change adds a key-listener to navigate between test rectangles on
the timeline. When an out-of-view test is selected, the timeline will
refocus and bring it into view. Functionality for left and right arrow
keys is supported, up and down (to navigate between workers) key are
not supported, but may be added in a future patch.

Change-Id: I4a187a1c048d5e6552316d10db0c677432aa8f7e

commit_message:
Change default endpoint for Keystone v3 to public

All of the other Openstack services have a 'public' default endpoint
type. Keystone has 'admin' default endpoint type. Why not make
Keystone compliant and change the default for Keystone v3 from 'admin'
to 'public'. Keystone v2 will remain the same with an 'admin' default.

Closes-Bug: #1457702
Change-Id: I515438477dba72c2a0c4595603000690511b5700

commit_message:
Add betamax to test-requirements.txt

While running tests via `python setup.py test` has never really
been supported by keystoneauth, betamax to the test requirements
does enable this.

For the record, testing is meant to be run via tox and is only
ever confirmed to work via tox. Using methods outside of tox
are not guaranteed to work and will continue to remain untested.

Change-Id: I0256369acb6697f7d8b94126787dd21e82087f90
Closes-Bug: #1523893

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-12-08 17:46:12.000000000', 'files': ['keystone/tests/unit/test_backend.py'], 'message': "Verify that attribute `enabled` equals True

In change I2b67c34796c54b0963fbc7020d4e78ed4f71c7f3 all occurences of
assertEqual(True, ...) were changed to assertTrue(...). Although it's
fine for most of the changes, one of them should have stayed as it is,
because assertTrue converts the passed argument to bool(). So, a call
assertTrue(-42) is the same as assertTrue(bool(-42)), and we want
AssertionError to be raised in this case.

to change it.

commit_message:
Verify that attribute `enabled` equals True

In change I2b67c34796c54b0963fbc7020d4e78ed4f71c7f3 all occurences of
assertEqual(True, ...) were changed to assertTrue(...). Although it's
fine for most of the changes, one of them should have stayed as it is,
because assertTrue converts the passed argument to bool(). So, a call
assertTrue(-42) is the same as assertTrue(bool(-42)), and we want
AssertionError to be raised in this case.

Use assertIs instead of assertTrue were appropriate. Tell others not
to change it.

Change-Id: Ifec683e7b5b728244f0444aa24a90994b1ce5153

commit_message:
More useful message when using direct driver import

In the Liberty release, we switched to using entrypoints for
specifying the driver or auth plugin. The deprecation message
didn't mention the driver name that was specified, nor did it
mention where to look for the expected names, so it was not
user friendly.

commit_message:
Add oslo.config compatibility attributes

In trying to get the OpenStack server projects to consume keystoneauth,
we ran in to the fact that they want to treat the things registered with
"register_conf_options" as oslo.config objects. It works fine that they
aren't - except that an oslo.config option has an attribute called
'deprecated_opts' while ours is called 'deprecated'. The same is true
of the other three attributes added.

Change-Id: I7d53c17d518b01946e091702a582648998c2ae17

revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-11-10 11:35:08.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/agent/l3/router_info.py', 'neutron/tests/unit/agent/l3/test_agent.py'], 'message': "Don't snat traffic between fixed IPs behind same router

This fixes a bug where an iptables rule to not snat traffic between
fixed IPs is only being added if enable_snat=true. We should add
this rule no matter what the value is for enable_snat.

Without this patch, current code will break such use case:
2 fixed IPs behind same router both have floatingip associated. And
the router has enable_snat=false. When fixed IP A want to ping
fixed IP B, fixed IP A will get the reply from fixed IP B's floating
IP.

More details could be found at bug description.

Change-Id: I322e8d454ef1d529ceda541fb5fe577cd70b412f
Closes-bug: #1505781
"}]
commit_message:
Don't snat traffic between fixed IPs behind same router

This fixes a bug where an iptables rule to not snat traffic between
fixed IPs is only being added if enable_snat=true. We should add
this rule no matter what the value is for enable_snat.

Without this patch, current code will break such use case:
2 fixed IPs behind same router both have floatingip associated. And
the router has enable_snat=false. When fixed IP A want to ping
fixed IP B, fixed IP A will get the reply from fixed IP B's floating
IP.

More details could be found at bug description.

Change-Id: I322e8d454ef1d529ceda541fb5fe577cd70b412f
Closes-bug: #1505781

commit_message:
Fix 500 error when no fernet token is passed

Keystone returns internal server error if the
user doesn't send any token. This happens only for
fernet token. This review returns 401 if the token
is not passed. Logic is moved from provider to
controller layer.

Since the logic has movoed to controller, some
of code which directly checks for no token in
the provider and their corresponding  tests
has been removed from the token providers
as they are redundant.

Closes-Bug: 1526976

Change-Id: I0b6b0c48d6c841f996d1b8711d6c343ddfd5d945
(cherry picked from commit 171f0e2193f336c02646e4366764d53336b10c8b)

commit_message:
Allow to use the old deploy ramdisk

While defaulting to IPA is a correct choice, for the transition period
let's allow people to use the old ramdisk. Adds new option --old-deploy-image
to the upload command and move the deprecation message to it.

This change does not correspond to a Mitaka change, as in Mitaka the old
ramdisk should not be supported.

Change-Id: I311843ed95d23dfdc83d184a09c52f0f5e1b31df
Closes-Bug: #1530883

subject: Make Keystone_endpoint match service by name/type
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-01-06 17:09:03.000000000', 'files': ['spec/classes/trove_keystone_auth_spec.rb', 'manifests/taskmanager.pp', 'manifests/keystone/auth.pp'], 'message': 'Make Keystone_endpoint match service by name/type

Since a chance in puppet-keystone (1], we now match an endpoint with a
service name/type.
)
[1] http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/puppet-keystone/commit/?id=0a4e06abb0f5b3f324464ff5219d2885816311ce

Also:
require package before config file Before trying to build the guestagent
config file from the template with Puppet, first install the package so
we make sure /etc/trove is ready. Otherwise, Puppet will randomly fail
to create the file, if the package is not installed yet.

We need to squash the two changes otherwise CI will never pass.
Change-Id: I9662c684c83933ffe6ede0337bc1770dd65b0ce7
Closes-Bug: #1528308
'}]
commit_message:
Make Keystone_endpoint match service by name/type

Since a chance in puppet-keystone (1], we now match an endpoint with a
service name/type.
)
[1] http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/puppet-keystone/commit/?id=0a4e06abb0f5b3f324464ff5219d2885816311ce

Also:
require package before config file Before trying to build the guestagent
config file from the template with Puppet, first install the package so
we make sure /etc/trove is ready. Otherwise, Puppet will randomly fail
to create the file, if the package is not installed yet.

We need to squash the two changes otherwise CI will never pass.
Change-Id: I9662c684c83933ffe6ede0337bc1770dd65b0ce7
Closes-Bug: #1528308

It can be quite useful to know exactly how long each
filter is running and how long its operations are taking.

To be able to diagnosis slow filters and to know which

'}]
commit_message:
Add timing logging around each filter being ran

It can be quite useful to know exactly how long each
filter is running and how long its operations are taking.

To be able to diagnosis slow filters and to know which
filter may or may not be a bottleneck augment the current
messages and log statements with timing information that
shows how long the filter application took.

Change-Id: Ie5b12c667f55656d82c686e3fc62922be27b3965

commit_message:
Add Quota RUD and missing properties

Update the Quoto object to support read, update and delete. In
addition, explicitly parse the subnet_pools, security_group_rules,
security_groups and rbac_policies properties for the Quota object.
These changes are based on the networking v2 API [1].

[1] http://developer.openstack.org/api-ref-networking-v2-ext.html

Change-Id: I93a6969e271521595c8a109e22bce0b6486196fa
Closes-Bug: #1528249

commit_message:
Support extra dependencies when setup_develop

Recent pip supports using [extras] to install extra dependencies
from the project setup.cfg. Add support so that projects can take
advantage of it.

For example, if devstack is configured to use ldap, install the
extra ldap dependencies using:

 setup_develop $KEYSTONE_DIR ldap

Partial-Bug: 1479962
Change-Id: Ic13d95b99aaa4d3854b2723343e90f5de6b98aa2

commit_message:
Fix CI Tempest jobs

After merge of change [1] to devstack project, preconfigured creds for
Tempest cannot be used anymore. But Manila requires such.
For the moment, latest Tempest interfaces cannot allow us to use
preconfigured creds because of bug #1524717.
So, until this bug fixed, we should workaround Devstack changes and
set legacy opts explicitly.

[1] I65b56ff681d6c27094380693c953fbc3664eceb0

Related-Bug: #1531049
Closes-Bug: #1531189
Change-Id: I4dc266713ec06bc6e98616a1277c8ae6cadf199d

commit_message:
Trap and expose exception any 'args'

Exceptions that are raised and derive from base exception
provide a 'args' attribute (defined to be a tuple of arguments
given to the exception constructor) that we should do our best to
capture and provide for introspection purposes.

Change-Id: I6349f726ccf0248a08be90e43f63260c5bcc81df

commit_message:
Use keystoneauth instead of keystoneclient

keystoneauth was split out last cycle as a library specifically to deal
with doing auth functions so that people who do not need to do keystone
CRUD operations can just consume only the auth session parts. As part
of modernizing keystone interactions, use keystoneauth instead of
keystoneclient.

Change-Id: Ief82837103450de209fcbbd92d8f4e898949fac4

commit_message:
[ceph] Deploy ceph failed at controller node for multiple node

Controller node wouldn't install libvirt package. The package will only
been installed at nodes which had enable nova-compute.
We only need to configure libvirt secret if it had enable nova-compute.

Change-Id: I9cd6baf1820ce9f71c276d7e8b670307833578a5

commit_message:
Make image_list.sh independent of host IP address

We do not need the HOST_IP to be detected in order to be able to list
our images. So just set that to some dummy value before sourcing
functions.

This will allow tools like disk-image-builder to work regardless of
whether get_default_host_ip succeeds or not.

Change-Id: I9c22d2066e34309e70e56076e3d17c5db6ecee06

subject: Make logfile symlinks with relative names.
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-12-09 12:54:10.000000000', 'files': ['functions-common'], 'message': "Make logfile symlinks with relative names.

Using absolute names for the symlink breaks in quite a few ways;
 * when creating a tar file of the logs,
 * when serving via NFS,

or any other case where the directory gets transferred to
a different machine.

So just create the symlink with relative names, then they'll work
in any location.

Change-Id: I432a69754985fc71feb0068b7adca01066d7bc1b
"}]
commit_message:
Make logfile symlinks with relative names.

Using absolute names for the symlink breaks in quite a few ways;
 * when creating a tar file of the logs,
 * when serving via NFS,

or any other case where the directory gets transferred to
a different machine.

So just create the symlink with relative names, then they'll work
in any location.

Change-Id: I432a69754985fc71feb0068b7adca01066d7bc1b

subject: Fix restoring a backup volume to a larger volume
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-12-23 14:43:26.000000000', 'files': ['lib/cinder_backends/ceph'], 'message': 'Fix restoring a backup volume to a larger volume

We cannot restore a backup to a larger volume on ceph because it
fails with status "error_restoring". This patch adds read/write
permissions to volumes pool for backup user. We need such permissions
to change volume size during restoring backup when the backup is
smaller than a volume.

Change-Id: I794c1126bcee4e07baf5a9dcfee779fd61da5636
Closes-Bug: 1519749
'}]
commit_message:
Fix restoring a backup volume to a larger volume

We cannot restore a backup to a larger volume on ceph because it
fails with status "error_restoring". This patch adds read/write
permissions to volumes pool for backup user. We need such permissions
to change volume size during restoring backup when the backup is
smaller than a volume.

Change-Id: I794c1126bcee4e07baf5a9dcfee779fd61da5636
Closes-Bug: 1519749

subject: Use a swapfile if no swap and no ephemeral disk
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-01-06 17:55:54.000000000', 'files': ['functions.sh'], 'message': "Use a swapfile if no swap and no ephemeral disk

Some tests rely on swapping (this should also be addressed) so we need
to create swap of some sort when we don't have swap and don't have an
ephemeral disk to rely on. In these cases just use a swapfile.

Change-Id: I0eecdea3c8517955d961689ae7aacbdd7f690d3f
"}]
commit_message:
Use a swapfile if no swap and no ephemeral disk

Some tests rely on swapping (this should also be addressed) so we need
to create swap of some sort when we don't have swap and don't have an
ephemeral disk to rely on. In these cases just use a swapfile.

Change-Id: I0eecdea3c8517955d961689ae7aacbdd7f690d3f

commit_message:
Enable Equallogic Backends in Cinder

Enables support for configuring Cinder with a Dell
Equallogic storage backend.
This change adds all relevant parameters for:
 - Equallogic PS-Series (iSCSI)

Change-Id: Ia0f71863cfb12f2cdda43dcf707a9a7145963001

commit_message:
Wrong usage of "a/an"

Wrong usage of "a/an" in the messages:
"string that is the id field for an pre-existing"
"build a etree.XML object filling certain"

Should be:
"string that is the id field for a pre-existing"
"build an etree.XML object filling certain"

Totally 2 occurrences in python-keystoneclient base code.

Change-Id: Icef5247672f95af87375a4a135a961aefb0a4906

commit_message:
Use ironic-lib's util methods

ironic.common.utils.dd(), mkfs(), unlink_without_raise(),
and is_http_url() methods were moved to ironic-lib. This
removes the copies in ironic and updates the code to use
the methods in ironic-lib.

Change-Id: I09c0a037b7979079cbfe5e33cbfd157ea3f3f79d

commit_message:
[Docs] Fix metavars

 - added custom metavars
 - added generator for metavars

Before this patch:
$ rally task start --help
...
optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --deployment ACTION_KWARG_DEPLOYMENT
                        UUID or name of the deployment
  --task ACTION_KWARG_TASK, --filename ACTION_KWARG_TASK
                        Path to the input task file
  --task-args ACTION_KWARG_TASK_ARGS
                        Input task args (dict in json). These args are used to
                        render input task that is jinja2 template.
  --task-args-file ACTION_KWARG_TASK_ARGS_FILE
                        Path to the file with input task args (dict in
                        json/yaml). These args are used to render input task
                        that is jinja2 template.
  --tag ACTION_KWARG_TAG
                        Tag for this task
  --no-use              Don't set new task as default for future operations
  --abort-on-sla-failure
                        Abort the execution of a benchmark scenario whenany
                        SLA check for it fails

After:
$ rally task start --help
...
optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --deployment <uuid>
                        UUID or name of the deployment
  --task <path>, --filename <path>
                        Path to the input task file
  --task-args <json>
                        Input task args (dict in json). These args are used to
                        render input task that is jinja2 template.
  --task-args-file <path>
                        Path to the file with input task args (dict in
                        json/yaml). These args are used to render input task
                        that is jinja2 template.
  --tag <tag>           Tag for this task
  --no-use              Don't set new task as default for future operations
  --abort-on-sla-failure
                        Abort the execution of a benchmark scenario whenany
                        SLA check for it fails

Change-Id: I7a059eb151aecf219496a43f8427b64c0265b3ad

commit_message:
Add Fujitsu ETERNUS DX Volume Driver (again)

This driver supports FUJITSU Storage ETERNUS DX.
The volume driver for ETERNUS DX dropped at Kilo,
because we could not prepare 3rd party CI until deadline (Kilo-3).
I upload it again for Mitaka release.

[Supported Protocol]
 - iSCSI

[Supported Feature]
 - Volume Create/Delete
 - Volume Attach/Detach
 - Snapshot Create/Delete
 - Create Volume from Snapshot
 - Get Volume Stats
 - Copy Image to Volume,
 - Copy Volume to Image
 - Clone Volume
 - Extend Volume

DocImpact
Change-Id: Iea6ed679616ccf4bd7aa0c5f6ad6067aa1bed7f6
Implements: blueprint fujitsu-eternus-dx-driver

commit_message:
taskmanager: require package before config file

Before trying to build the guestagent config file from the template with
Puppet, first install the package so we make sure /etc/trove is ready.

Otherwise, Puppet will randomly fail to create the file, if the package
is not installed yet.

Change-Id: I65518d53d98aa114f8e5803910b3266d9b68e491

commit_message:
Change L3 agent delete HA-router Sequence

This patch will change the sequence of events in delete ha-router.
First ha router namespace is deleted then keepalived is disabled
which ends up in keepalive running out of control.

this change happened accidently in patch [1]

[1]https://review.openstack.org/#/c/217564/7

Change-Id: I6e266f30409cdd6669bff3effca1f55d8de68207
Closes-Bug: #1510759

commit_message:
Be consistent in how we give error codes in the Identity spec

Throughout the spec, we use various ways of given the HTTP error
codes, sometimes quoted, sometimes not, sometimes with the "HTTP"
moniker, sometimes not.

This patch makes this consistent, using the form:

HTTP ``400 Bad Request``

No actual changes to the error code being returned are being
made, this is just about formatting the document.

Change-Id: Icc21ebd1262ae889c7dcc4ee43ad203d52bcab0d

commit_message:
Use configured datastore on instance creation

The datastore and its version is now always passed on instance creation for
integration tests.
Previously the default datastore (and version) were used, ignoring the
settings in the test configuration.

Change-Id: Ib3e78bb68aaf992177b9d9cd1d89e84fb54830ed
Depends-On: Ifa4496eb1c9e2fe053978c708e7fa1069f12cb3f

commit_message:
Put py34 first in the env order of tox and remove py33

To solve the problem of "db type could
not be determined" on py34 we have to run first the py34 env to, then, run
py27. This patch puts py34 first on the tox.ini list of envs to avoid this
problem to happen.

Change-Id: I135cbbfcfb148ba845af43634d41951e118067f9
Closes-bug: #1489059

commit_message:
In port_dead, handle case when port already deleted

db_get_val can return None if the port got deleted concurrently.
In this case there is no need to mark it dead and add drop flow for it.

Change-Id: I5ef9665770df3a9bbaf79049b219fadd73e20309
Partial-Bug: #1493414
(cherry picked from commit 76cc53c611a639d915761d1fa3c879cda2ba3502)

commit_message:
Add keylistener to navigate tests on timeline

Adds an arrow key listener (for left and right arrows) on the timeline.
Once a test is selected, the arrow keys can be used to select adjacent
tests on the same worker thread. This helps select tests with small
run times that may be difficult to select using only the mouse.

Change-Id: Ia1691ef9e85d1f8e54e37ea8cbcd3834fe5064fb

commit_message:
Put py34 first in the env order of tox

To solve the problem of "db type could
not be determined" on py34 we have to run first the py34 env to, then, run
py27. This patch puts py34 first on the tox.ini list of envs to avoid this
problem to happen.

Change-Id: I461e4f0d931a9bbc37670dc2cd70d94f86acfb24
Closes-bug: #1489059

commit_message:
Use Horizon's plugin registration system

Magnum UI and their panels are currently registered via their `dashboard.py`
and `panel.py` files, but should use the enabled files.
This is standard in Horizon.

This patch changes registration method to enabled files.

For moving our dashboard to under the "project" dashbaord,
we need to change URLs. So, many files will be changed.

Since "/project/containers" is already used by Swift Container panel,
this patch uses "bays", "baymodels" and "bays/containers" for URLs.

Change-Id: Icedb984331bd46540f2e7d12bbefcc308aff214f
Closes-Bug: #1507679

commit_message:
Fix reclaim_instance_interval < 0 never delete instance completely

CONF.reclaim_instance_interval is interval in seconds for reclaiming
deleted instances. It should take effect only when value is greater
than 0. But current when set it with -1 for example, it will pass check
if we should soft delete an instance, but can't pass check whether should
clean soft deleted instance, then never have chance to clean up a soft deleted
instance and release the quota.
This commit sets CONF.reclaim_instance_interval's minimum value to 0.

Closes-Bug: #1518848

Change-Id: Idd8faad1a40f8898a9471504e664c3676b1b0e06

This refactors the single timeline directive into four separate

commit_message:
Refactor the timeline directive.

Presently the timeline directive is a single gigantic directive
containing all of the timeline code. Given the amount of code
involved, this complicates maintenance and makes it excessively
difficult to improve.

This refactors the single timeline directive into four separate
collaborating directives: a controller, an overview, a viewport,
and dstat charts. Each child directive is functionally separate
from the others, but can communicate with other chart components
via the controller. This separation should greatly improve future
maintenance, and has already led to several (included) bug fixes.

Change-Id: Id11d15a34466e42c5ebc9808717d52b468245e3a

commit_message:
Remove boto deprecation warnings in the unit tests

The following boto warning appears a couple of times in the unit test
logs.

    PendingDeprecationWarning: The current get_all_instances
implementation will be replaced with get_all_reservations.

Remove the warnings by replacing get_all_instances with
get_all_reservations, as the boto docs suggest. Also note that
get_all_instances just calls get_all_reservations at the moment anyway.

    "This method's current behavior is deprecated in favor of
get_all_reservations. A future major release will change
get_all_instances to return a list of Instance objects as its name
suggests."

https://github.com/boto/boto/blob/8a025df86554a555cb4b58357803f4df044e2c6f/boto/ec2/connection.py#L580

Change-Id: I2a3f6d4c2a3ce9944dc0cb30377e23c62a68fe40

commit_message:
Support DB clustering configuration

You can specify ['ip1:port', 'ip2:port', 'ip3:port'] list in the
configuration file.

If only one server exists, just set it to ['ip:port'].

This option is the same to rabbitmq configuration.

In addition, the whole oslo.cfg object is passed to db driver layer
in order to let developers decide which option to use.

Change-Id: I44fcf0af5a7740af720557bc7a0c60fcf389a416
Implements: bp zookeeper-driver
Closes-Bug: #1529325

subject: Don’t log warnings for image cache when disabled
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-01-05 01:31:59.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/volume/flows/manager/create_volume.py'], 'message': 'Don’t log warnings for image cache when disabled

Right now we do a check for the internal tenant and log a warning before
we check to see if the cache is even turned on for that backend. We
should be only checking for the internal tenant if the image cache has
been configured for the backend.

In addition we shouldn’t log a warning for this since there is already
a warning for the internal context when we try and create it if it is
not configured correctly… to reduce the warning spam this change
switches the log message to an info level.

Change-Id: Iddc4648543d268a4b3b8d557c94c4d2876654e22
Closes-Bug: #1530964
'}]
commit_message:
Don’t log warnings for image cache when disabled

Right now we do a check for the internal tenant and log a warning before
we check to see if the cache is even turned on for that backend. We
should be only checking for the internal tenant if the image cache has
been configured for the backend.

In addition we shouldn’t log a warning for this since there is already
a warning for the internal context when we try and create it if it is
not configured correctly… to reduce the warning spam this change
switches the log message to an info level.

Change-Id: Iddc4648543d268a4b3b8d557c94c4d2876654e22
Closes-Bug: #1530964

commit_message:
VMware: add in folder support on VC

In an effort to provide more information to VC admins we create a
a folder that will contain the OpenStack information. VM's will be
put in the following folder:
    Openstack/Project (<project-id>)/Instances

Until this patch the VM's were put in the root folder.

NOTE: the code is backward compatible. All newly created instances
will be placed in the aforementioned folder. Existing instances will
continue to work as usual.

This is the first part of the blueprint vmware-better-display-names

Change-Id: I6c653cf580e844f121a6566c4f2cbe320531f4e4

commit_message:
Clarify project hierarchy and parent usage within the API

The current description was not clear in a few areas:

- The fact that you can use parent_id on create to imply which
  domain the entity is in
- How entities created via the domain API compare with those
  projects acting as domains created via the project API
- How root domains are handled
- The fact that all projects are now part of a hierarchy

This patch clarifies the above and restructures the relevent
sections to make them more readible given the changes.

Change-Id: Ib9390cd71f111ed6e3131013d4a956db57d1d5ec
Partially-Implements: bp reseller

commit_message:
Optimize simulator.py for better throughput

* Avoid string concatenation during logging, especially
  when logging level is disabled.
* Initialize the Randomized strings we will be using
  as payloads *before* we start sending the messages
  as the string creation takes time and reduces
  throughput

Change-Id: I546229fe7ade95572e11bcda95a587228d84bc28
